# Kern — project rules

## Sources of truth

- **Product & technical spec:** [Kern PRD.md](../../Kern%20PRD.md). Entry point for agents: [KERN_PRD_SPEC.md](../../KERN_PRD_SPEC.md) (points at the PRD).
- **Build plan & prompts:** [Phases.md](../../Phases.md). Implement tasks in dependency order (Phase 1: tasks 1.1 through 1.16 unless directed otherwise).

## Stack

Match the PRD: React 18+, Vite 5+, TypeScript (`strict: true`), Tailwind, Radix UI, TanStack Query v5, TanStack Table, Zustand, React Router v6, Supabase JS v2, cmdk, and other listed libraries. Do not add packages without explicit approval.

## Database

When the schema changes: add migrations **and** regenerate the typed Supabase client / shared DB types **in the same task**, per Phases.md. Follow RLS policies and table definitions from the PRD.

## Environment

Use `.env.example` and placeholders in docs; never commit real secrets. State whether Supabase is **local** (`supabase start`) or **remote** when running tasks that depend on URLs/keys.

## Session handoff

Prefix task prompts with the template in [SESSION_OPENER.md](../../SESSION_OPENER.md) (task id, last completed task, environment notes).
